The paper discusses the ranking of Wikipedia articles in search engines, which is a topic related to information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also discusses the quality of encyclopedic entries, which could fall under the category of digital libraries (cs.DL) or human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper proposes a heuristic method for evaluating Wikipedia entries, which could be related to computational linguistics (cs.CL). Finally, the paper discusses the relevance judgments of jurors, which could be related to cybersecurity (cs.CY) in terms of evaluating the trustworthiness of online information.
